dublin_core.dcvalue: Leadership is consistently identified as an important factor that influences nurses adoption of health information technologies yet the concept of leadership remains underdeveloped Our study examines the influence of leadership on nurses mHealth usage outcomes Informed by diverse fields we developed the MOBILE Nurse conceptual model as a way to empirically explore relationships between leadership and other factors commonly thought to influence mHealth usage in nursing
Studies in health technology and informatics
The MOBile-Health and Implementation Leadership Evaluation (MOBILE) Nurse Study: Developing a Testable Conceptual Model.
